<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1710,2025]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
The nomenclature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2002" box="[395,726,1710,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Aeshna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevistyla" subSpecies="caledonica">
<emphasis box="[395,726,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Aeshna brevistyla caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
requires some consideration. The species is predominantly reported in the contemporary literature under the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1992" box="[762,932,1746,1772]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Adversaeschna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[762,932,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Adversaeschna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This name was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, J." box="[1270,1436,1746,1773]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="453 - 471" refId="ref36740" refString="Watson, J. (1992) The affinities of Aeshna brevistyla (Rambur) (Anisoptera: Aeshnidae). Odonatologica, 21, 453 - 471." type="journal article" year="1992">Watson (1992)</bibRefCitation>
who analysed the species’ affinities and suggested a subgeneric status within 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[1023,1105,1782,1808]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Aeshna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1023,1105,1782,1808]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Aeshna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The name was subsequently given a full generic status without further justification and is used to denote not only the New Caledonian populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[242,382,1854,1881]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Aeshna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevistyla">
<emphasis box="[242,382,1854,1881]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">A. brevistyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(probably due to 
<bibRefCitation author="Davies, D. A. L." box="[581,740,1854,1880]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="229 - 251" refId="ref31736" refString="Davies, D. A. L. (2002) The odonate fauna of New Caledonia, including the descriptions of a new species and a new subspecies. Odonatologica, 31, 229 - 251." type="journal article" year="2002">Davies (2002)</bibRefCitation>
who used it for the first time), but also Australian ones. Given the lack of published evidence to justify the elevation of this name to genus rank, we treat 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Watson" authorityYear="1992" box="[1162,1332,1890,1916]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Adversaeschna" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Metazoa" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1162,1332,1890,1916]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Adversaeschna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subgenus, as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Watson, J." box="[405,570,1926,1953]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" pagination="453 - 471" refId="ref36740" refString="Watson, J. (1992) The affinities of Aeshna brevistyla (Rambur) (Anisoptera: Aeshnidae). Odonatologica, 21, 453 - 471." type="journal article" year="1992">Watson (1992)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rambur" authorityYear="1842" box="[617,815,1926,1952]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Aeshna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevistyla">
<emphasis box="[617,815,1926,1952]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Aeshna brevistyla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation box="[830,913,1926,1952]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="5.[151,239,483,509]" captionTargetBox="[161,1911,626,1699]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 1. Odonata fauna of New Caledonia arranged chronologically with the original published binomial name, the currently valid binomial name, locality of first New Caledonian record, literature source and page (species described as new to science based on holotypes from New Caledonia are marked with an asterisk after the valid species name)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF47D8E6FFA5FF81FF1AB9D461EBFD92" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" tableUuid="DF47D8E6FFA5FF81FF1AB9D461EBFD92">Table 1</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="44" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1710,2025]" lastBlockId="42.[151,1437,152,251]" lastPageId="42" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1961,1988]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[363,449,1962,1988]" captionStart="FIGURE 40" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1098,1123]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,151,1079]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[151,1436,151,1079]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 40. Records of Aeshna brevistyla caledonica." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3342321/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
). A New Caledonian endemic subspecies, belonging to a monotypic subgenus that occurs elsewhere in 
<collectingCountry box="[351,457,1998,2024]" name="Australia" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Australia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[467,620,1998,2025]" name="New Zealand" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
, Norfolk Islands, Raul Island in the Kermadec Archipelago, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1344,1436,1999,2025]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lieftinck, M." box="[158,331,152,179]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" pagination="127 - 166" refId="ref33785" refString="Lieftinck, M. (1975) The dragonflies (Odonata) of New Caledonia and the Loyalty Islands - Part 1. Imagines. Cahiers Office de la recherche scientifique et technique outre-mer (ORSTOM), Serie Hydrobiologie, 9, 127 - 166." type="journal article" year="1975">Lieftinck 1975</bibRefCitation>
). The subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Davies" authorityYear="2002" box="[528,800,153,179]" class="Insecta" family="Aeshnidae" genus="Aeshna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="brevistyla" subSpecies="caledonica">
<emphasis box="[528,800,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">A. brevistyla caledonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from more than 20 localities in the Province Sud, with important populations in the Plaine des Lacs. One specimen collected at Anse Vata in Nouméa is in the 
<collectionCode box="[151,230,225,251]" country="New Caledonia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/crvj-94ys" name="Office de la Recherche Scientifique et Technique d'Outre-Mer" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">ONNC</collectionCode>
collection.
</paragraph>
